(
<figureCitation id="13212FC3521BFFC300CCFA24FDDFFA11" box="[506,614,1444,1471]" captionStart-0="Figs 1–6" captionStart-1="Figs 7–11" captionStartId-0="1.[174,213,1317,1339]" captionStartId-1="2.[167,206,931,953]" captionTargetBox-0="[219,1202,174,1296]" captionTargetBox-1="[203,1186,174,918]" captionTargetId-0="figure-193@1.[219,1202,174,1303]" captionTargetId-1="figure-230@2.[203,1186,174,918]" captionTargetPageId-0="1" captionTargetPageId-1="2" captionText-0="Figs 1–6. Somatic characters of the holotype of Sahastata amethystina sp. n.: 1–2 — live specimen, dorsal and frontal; 3–4 — preserved specimen, lateral and dorsal; 5–6 — prosoma, dorsal and ventral. Photographs 1–2 after Ali Mohajeran." captionText-1="Figs 7–11. Endogyne and legs of the holotype of Sahastata amethystina sp. n.: 7, 9 — endogyne, dorsal, different aspects; 8 — right receptacle, dorsal; 10 — proximal part of metatarsus IV with calamistrum, dorsal; 11 tibia II, showing ventral spines. Scale bar 0.2 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453781" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453783" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6453781/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6453783/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="267">figs 1–11</figureCitation>
)
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA53346521BFFC301EDFA5DFD88F9A3" blockId="0.[166,1224,1499,1549]" pageId="0" pageNumber="267">
<materialsCitation id="3B72391B521BFFC301EDFA5DFD94F9A3" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3753057301" collectingDate="2015-12" collectionCode="SMF" collectorName="S. Sami" country="Iran" latitude="27.960556" location="Kahnuj-Faryab" longitude="57.584444" pageId="0" pageNumber="267" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Kerman" typeStatus="holotype">
T y p e m a t e r i a l. 
<typeStatus id="54A18DE4521BFFC300ACFA5DFE4DFA5D" box="[410,500,1501,1523]" pageId="0" pageNumber="267">Holotype</typeStatus>
ǫ (
<collectionCode id="ED0BAB83521BFFC30320FA5DFDF0FA5D" box="[534,585,1501,1523]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34838" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34838" name="Forschungsinstitut und Natur-Museum Senckenberg" pageId="0" pageNumber="267">SMF</collectionCode>
), 
<collectingCountry id="F30D73D6521BFFC3036FFA5DFD3DFA5D" box="[601,644,1501,1523]" name="Iran" pageId="0" pageNumber="267">Iran</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49DEFDA4521BFFC303BBFA5DFD65FA5D" box="[653,732,1501,1523]" pageId="0" pageNumber="267">Kerman</collectingRegion>
Province, vicinity of 
<location id="8EC5659D521BFFC3029FFA5DFB82FA5D" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B38250521BFFC10190FA23FC54F923:8EC5659D521BFFC3029FFA5DFB82FA5D" box="[937,1083,1501,1523]" country="Iran" name="Kahnuj-Faryab" pageId="0" pageNumber="267" stateProvince="Kerman">Kahnuj-Faryab</location>
Rd., 27̊57'38&quot; 
<subSubSection id="C30060CD521BFFC10190FA77FC54F923" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="269" pageId="0" pageNumber="267" type="description">
N 57̊35'04&quot; E, 
<date id="FFA41586521BFFC30001FA77FE77F9A3" box="[311,462,1527,1549]" pageId="0" pageNumber="267" value="2015-12">
<collectingDate id="EFE0EC6E521BFFC30001FA77FE77F9A3" box="[311,462,1527,1549]" pageId="0" pageNumber="267" value="2015-12">December 2015</collectingDate>
</date>
(
<collectorName id="26EF5690521BFFC300EDFA77FD9FF9A3" box="[475,550,1527,1549]" pageId="0" pageNumber="267">S. Sami</collectorName>
). 
<paragraph id="8BA53346521BFFC301EDF9B4FCDBF9C1" blockId="0.[166,1225,1588,1839]" pageId="0" pageNumber="267">
E t y m o l o g y. The specific epithet is derived from the Latin “ 
<emphasis id="B96EEF54521BFFC30295F9B4FB84F9E0" box="[931,1085,1588,1614]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="267">amethystinus</emphasis>
”, and refers to the amethyst colouring of the carapace in live specimens.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA53346521BFFC201EDF9F4FEC2FA44" blockId="0.[166,1225,1588,1839]" lastBlockId="1.[174,1233,1423,1834]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="268" pageId="0" pageNumber="267">
D i a g n o s i s. The new species is easily differentiated from the 
<typeStatus id="54A18DE4521BFFC302E6F9F4FBBBF921" box="[976,1026,1652,1679]" pageId="0" pageNumber="267">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A48C5521BFFC30558F9F4FEEDF901" authority="(Simon, 1897)" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1897" class="Arachnida" family="Filistatidae" genus="Sahastata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="267" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis id="B96EEF54521BFFC30558F9F4FB70F920" box="[1134,1225,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="267">S. nigra</emphasis>
(Simon, 1897)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A48C5521BFFC300ABF914FBA2F901" authority="Marusik, Zamani &amp; Mirshamsi, 2014" authorityName="Marusik, Zamani &amp; Mirshamsi" authorityYear="2014" box="[413,1051,1684,1711]" class="Arachnida" family="Filistatidae" genus="Sahastata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="267" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinuspersica">
<emphasis id="B96EEF54521BFFC300ABF914FDF0F900" box="[413,585,1684,1710]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="267">S. sinuspersica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8B4EB7521BFFC30363F914FBA2F901" author="Marusik, Yu. M. &amp; Zamani, A. &amp; Mirshamsi, O." box="[597,1051,1684,1711]" pageId="0" pageNumber="267" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref1455" refString="Marusik, Yu. M., Zamani, A., Mirshamsi, O. 2014. Three new species of mygalomorph and filistatid spiders from Iran (Araneae, Cyrtaucheniidae, Nemesiidae and Filistatidae). ZooKeys, 463, 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="2014">Marusik, Zamani &amp; Mirshamsi, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by the bright violet colour of the carapace (black or dark brown in other congeners), the shape of the calamistrum, comprising 3 rows of thick, short and tightly-spaced bristles directed longitudinally (
<figureCitation id="13212FC3521BFFC3006CF974FE1EF8A1" box="[346,423,1780,1807]" captionStart="Figs 7–11" captionStartId="2.[167,206,931,953]" captionTargetBox="[203,1186,174,918]" captionTargetId="figure-230@2.[203,1186,174,918]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 7–11. Endogyne and legs of the holotype of Sahastata amethystina sp. n.: 7, 9 — endogyne, dorsal, different aspects; 8 — right receptacle, dorsal; 10 — proximal part of metatarsus IV with calamistrum, dorsal; 11 tibia II, showing ventral spines. Scale bar 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453783" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453783/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="267">fig. 10</figureCitation>
), in contrast to 2 distinct rows of long, wavy bristles directed almost transversely in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A48C5521BFFC30060F894FE14F880" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[342,429,1812,1838]" class="Arachnida" family="Filistatidae" genus="Sahastata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="267" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis id="B96EEF54521BFFC30060F894FE14F880" box="[342,429,1812,1838]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="267">S. nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 3 distinct rows of thick setae directed diagonally in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A48C5521BFFC30515F894FB71F880" authorityName="Marusik, Zamani &amp; Mirshamsi" authorityYear="2014" box="[1059,1224,1812,1838]" class="Arachnida" family="Filistatidae" genus="Sahastata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="267" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinuspersica">
<emphasis id="B96EEF54521BFFC30515F894FB71F880" box="[1059,1224,1812,1838]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="267">S. sinuspersica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8B4EB7521AFFC20180FA0FFE10FA04" author="Marusik, Yu. M. &amp; Zamani, A. &amp; Mirshamsi, O." box="[182,425,1423,1450]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref1455" refString="Marusik, Yu. M., Zamani, A., Mirshamsi, O. 2014. Three new species of mygalomorph and filistatid spiders from Iran (Araneae, Cyrtaucheniidae, Nemesiidae and Filistatidae). ZooKeys, 463, 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="2014">Marusik et al., 2014</bibRefCitation>
: figs 26–29, 32, 33), and the complex shape of the receptacles, each having three distinct parts (globular or with two heads in sibling species, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8B4EB7521AFFC20512FA2FFF53FA44" author="Marusik, Yu. M. &amp; Zamani, A. &amp; Mirshamsi, O." pageId="1" pageNumber="268" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref1455" refString="Marusik, Yu. M., Zamani, A., Mirshamsi, O. 2014. Three new species of mygalomorph and filistatid spiders from Iran (Araneae, Cyrtaucheniidae, Nemesiidae and Filistatidae). ZooKeys, 463, 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="2014">Marusik et al., 2014</bibRefCitation>
: figs 34–41).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF6563CE521AFFC20198FAA5FECBFADE" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453781" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6453781" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453781/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" startId="1.[174,213,1317,1339]" targetBox="[219,1202,174,1296]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph id="8BA53346521AFFC20198FAA5FECBFADE" blockId="1.[174,1238,1317,1392]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">
Figs 1–6. Somatic characters of the holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A48C5521AFFC2034EFAA5FCE8FA94" authority="Marusik &amp; Zamani, 2016" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Zamani" authorityYear="2016" box="[632,849,1317,1338]" class="Arachnida" family="Filistatidae" genus="Sahastata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amethystina" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B96EEF54521AFFC2034EFAA5FCE8FA94" box="[632,849,1317,1338]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">Sahastata amethystina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25D522F521AFFC20261FAA5FC35FA95" box="[855,908,1317,1339]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: 1–2 — live specimen, dorsal and frontal; 3–4 — preserved specimen, lateral and dorsal; 5–6 — prosoma, dorsal and ventral. Photographs 1–2 after Ali Mohajeran.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BA53346521AFFC201D5FA6FFE6EF9E4" blockId="1.[174,1233,1423,1834]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">D e s c r i p t i o n. Female. Total length 15.0. Carapace 5.75 long, 4.25 wide; clypeus 0.63 long. Sternum 2.88 long, 2.59 wide; labium 1.15 long, 0.86 wide. Fovea deep conical, without distinct margins.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA53346521AFFC201D5F9CFFB7AF884" blockId="1.[174,1233,1423,1834]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">
Eye sizes and interdistances: AME 0.23, ALE 0.3, PME 0.26, PLE 0.27; AME-AME 0.16, PME-PME 0.33, PLE-ALE 0.11; anterior eye row 0.46, posterior eye row 0.57. Leg spination (apical spines not counted): I femur 1p, tibia 1p, 3-0v, metatarsus 1p, 3pv, 
<emphasis id="B96EEF54521AFFC20537F910FB98F907" box="[1025,1057,1680,1705]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">ca.</emphasis>
10v; II Ti 3-3v, metatarsus 3p, 3r or 1r, 
<emphasis id="B96EEF54521AFFC200FFF930FE50F967" box="[457,489,1712,1737]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">ca.</emphasis>
10v; III tibia 1d, 2p, 3r, 3-1v, metatarsus 4p, 3e, 
<emphasis id="B96EEF54521AFFC20512F930FBFCF967" box="[1060,1093,1712,1737]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">ca.</emphasis>
6v; IV tibia r1, 3-0v; metatarsus 2p or 0p, 
<emphasis id="B96EEF54521AFFC2032BF950FD87F947" box="[541,574,1744,1769]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">ca.</emphasis>
8v. Spines short (shorter than regular setae) and thick (
<figureCitation id="13212FC3521AFFC20183F96FFE98F8A4" box="[181,289,1775,1802]" captionStart-0="Figs 1–6" captionStart-1="Figs 7–11" captionStartId-0="1.[174,213,1317,1339]" captionStartId-1="2.[167,206,931,953]" captionTargetBox-0="[219,1202,174,1296]" captionTargetBox-1="[203,1186,174,918]" captionTargetId-0="figure-193@1.[219,1202,174,1303]" captionTargetId-1="figure-230@2.[203,1186,174,918]" captionTargetPageId-0="1" captionTargetPageId-1="2" captionText-0="Figs 1–6. Somatic characters of the holotype of Sahastata amethystina sp. n.: 1–2 — live specimen, dorsal and frontal; 3–4 — preserved specimen, lateral and dorsal; 5–6 — prosoma, dorsal and ventral. Photographs 1–2 after Ali Mohajeran." captionText-1="Figs 7–11. Endogyne and legs of the holotype of Sahastata amethystina sp. n.: 7, 9 — endogyne, dorsal, different aspects; 8 — right receptacle, dorsal; 10 — proximal part of metatarsus IV with calamistrum, dorsal; 11 tibia II, showing ventral spines. Scale bar 0.2 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453781" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453783" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6453781/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6453783/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">figs 2–11</figureCitation>
). Ventral spines not paired. Calamistrum comprises three rows of thick, tightlyspaced bristles directed along the axis of metatarsus, transverse section crosses four bristles.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF6563CE5219FFC10191FC23FD8EFC40" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453783" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6453783" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453783/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="269" startId="2.[167,206,931,953]" targetBox="[203,1186,174,918]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8BA533465219FFC10191FC23FD8EFC40" blockId="2.[166,1225,931,1006]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">
Figs 7–11. Endogyne and legs of the holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A48C55219FFC10346FC23FCFEFC16" authority="Marusik &amp; Zamani, 2016" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Zamani" authorityYear="2016" box="[624,839,931,952]" class="Arachnida" family="Filistatidae" genus="Sahastata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amethystina" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B96EEF545219FFC10346FC23FCFEFC16" box="[624,839,931,952]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">Sahastata amethystina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25D522F5219FFC1027AFC23FC39FC17" box="[844,896,931,953]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
