<paragraph id="8BA533465219FFC101EDFA92FE7FFA23" blockId="2.[166,1225,1298,1677]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">
Colouration in alcohol (
<figureCitation id="13212FC35219FFC100CAFA92FDE7FA83" box="[508,606,1298,1325]" captionStart="Figs 1–6" captionStartId="1.[174,213,1317,1339]" captionTargetBox="[219,1202,174,1296]" captionTargetId="figure-193@1.[219,1202,174,1303]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1–6. Somatic characters of the holotype of Sahastata amethystina sp. n.: 1–2 — live specimen, dorsal and frontal; 3–4 — preserved specimen, lateral and dorsal; 5–6 — prosoma, dorsal and ventral. Photographs 1–2 after Ali Mohajeran." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453781" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453781/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">figs 3, 4</figureCitation>
): carapace brown without distinct pattern, eye field dark, with dark median band from behind eye field to fovea; abdomen and legs uniformly dark brown. Colouration in live specimen (
<figureCitation id="13212FC35219FFC10393FAD2FCBDFAC3" box="[677,772,1362,1389]" captionStart="Figs 1–6" captionStartId="1.[174,213,1317,1339]" captionTargetBox="[219,1202,174,1296]" captionTargetId="figure-193@1.[219,1202,174,1303]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1–6. Somatic characters of the holotype of Sahastata amethystina sp. n.: 1–2 — live specimen, dorsal and frontal; 3–4 — preserved specimen, lateral and dorsal; 5–6 — prosoma, dorsal and ventral. Photographs 1–2 after Ali Mohajeran." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453781" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453781/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
): carapace bright violet, abdomen and legs dark violet (
<tableCitation id="C69806FD5219FFC10050FAF2FE0DFA23" box="[358,436,1394,1421]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="2.[166,237,1034,1055]" captionTargetBox="[174,1174,1087,1271]" captionTargetId="graphics-291@2.[166,1224,1077,1274]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Table 1. Lengths of palp and leg segments" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF6563CE5219FFC10190FB8AFDDAFBB1" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA533465219FFC101EDFA12FD81F9A3" blockId="2.[166,1225,1298,1677]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">
Endogyne as in 
<figureCitation id="13212FC35219FFC10094FA12FD92FA03" box="[418,555,1426,1453]" captionStart="Figs 7–11" captionStartId="2.[167,206,931,953]" captionTargetBox="[203,1186,174,918]" captionTargetId="figure-230@2.[203,1186,174,918]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 7–11. Endogyne and legs of the holotype of Sahastata amethystina sp. n.: 7, 9 — endogyne, dorsal, different aspects; 8 — right receptacle, dorsal; 10 — proximal part of metatarsus IV with calamistrum, dorsal; 11 tibia II, showing ventral spines. Scale bar 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453783" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453783/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">figures 7–9</figureCitation>
. Each receptacle subdivided into three parts, the inner digitiform arm (
<emphasis id="B96EEF545219FFC10051FA32FEC5FA65" box="[359,380,1458,1483]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">Ir</emphasis>
), triangular middle part (
<emphasis id="B96EEF545219FFC1039AFA32FD69FA65" box="[684,720,1458,1483]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">Mr</emphasis>
) and elongate oval lateral arms (
<emphasis id="B96EEF545219FFC10563FA32FBD6FA65" box="[1109,1135,1458,1483]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">Lr</emphasis>
). Inner and lateral arms are densely covered with glandular pores; pores with long cilia (longer than diameter of receptacle arms).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA533465219FFC101EDF992FE2CF983" blockId="2.[166,1225,1298,1677]" box="[219,405,1554,1581]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">Male unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA533465219FFC101EDF9B2FCBDF9C3" blockId="2.[166,1225,1298,1677]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">
H a b i t a t. The 
<typeStatus id="54A18DE45219FFC100AEF9B2FE46F9E3" box="[408,511,1586,1613]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected during the day from under a large stone in a dry, warm, rocky habitat of sparse 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A48C55219FFC1030AF9D2FD0AF9C3" box="[572,691,1618,1645]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="2" pageNumber="269" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Arecaceae</taxonomicName>
forest.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA533465219FFC101EDF9F2FC54F923" blockId="2.[166,1225,1298,1677]" box="[219,1005,1650,1677]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. The species is known only from the 
<typeStatus id="54A18DE45219FFC10261F9F2FC30F923" box="[855,905,1650,1677]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
